Package zuul.gameState

Class Inventory

java.lang.Object
zuul.gameState.Inventory
public class Inventory
extends java.lang.Object
An inventory to store each Item held by a Room or Character in the "World of Zuul" application.

    • items

      private java.util.ArrayList<Item> items
      List of all items stored in this Inventory. Multiple non-unique items can be stored.

      The maximum Item weight that can be stored in this Inventory.

      The default maximum Item weight to use is one if not specified during instantiation.

  • Constructor Details

    • Inventory

      public Inventory()
      Default constructor. Initialises empty Item list and sets the MAX_WEIGHT of this Inventory to the default value, 10.

    • Inventory

      public Inventory​(int maxWeight)
      Constructor with MAX_WEIGHT specified. Initialises empty Item list and sets the MAX_WEIGHT of this Inventory to the value specified.
      Parameters:
      maxWeight - the maximum Item weight that this inventory should be able to hold

  • Method Details

    • addItem

      public void addItem​(Item item)
      Adds an Item to this Inventory.

      No check is made on adding duplicate Items.

      Parameters:
      item - the Item to be added to this inventory, not null

    • removeItem

      public void removeItem​(Item item)
      Removes the specified Item from this Inventory. If more than one Item in this inventory equals the specified Item then the first occurrence is removed.
      Parameters:
      item - the Item to be removed, not null

    • getItemIndex

      public int getItemIndex​(Item item)
      Gets the index of the specified Item in this inventory. This method return regardless of if the item specified is in this inventory.
      Parameters:
      item - the item to check for, not null
      Returns:
      the index of item parameter if it exists in the array, -1 otherwise

    • getItem

      public java.util.Optional<Item> getItem​(Item item)

      Parameters:
      item - the Item to get, not null
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the requested Item if found, empty otherwise

    • getTotalWeight

    • containsItem

      public boolean containsItem​(Item item)

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Creates a String representing the contents of this inventory.

      Returns an empty String if this inventory is empty.

      Overrides:
      toString in class java.lang.Object
